        "cooked": "<p>Oh. In desktop, it says chat.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/1/21c779f58bc3f2c27bcb5225b5b82aeeab207944.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/21c779f58bc3f2c27bcb5225b5b82aeeab207944\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/1/21c779f58bc3f2c27bcb5225b5b82aeeab207944.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"4OP8ehmQpMc29yq5jgsHKu3GzQ0\" width=\"306\" height=\"170\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">306×170 3.94 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>Note that “fixed” is translated in the feminine, which would imply that it is a “conversa” and not a “chat”.</p>\n<p>And still, in other places, conversa, not chat, desktop.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/8/78eb55e0480646f18daab36880e698cb783cf06f.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/78eb55e0480646f18daab36880e698cb783cf06f\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/8/78eb55e0480646f18daab36880e698cb783cf06f.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"hfHv1ityjACfRzQrUOLLNlflaEL\" width=\"323\" height=\"238\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">323×238 4.41 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>I would go with conversa myself as to not fit into “estrangeirismo”.</p>",
